## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report

I've thoroughly explored the Palembang codebase to understand entity rendering, data flow, and styling. Here's a complete overview:

---

### 1. ENTITY TYPES & CONSTANTS

**Entity Kind Definition** (line 1, `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/shared/contracts.ts`):
```typescript
export type EntityKind = "workspace" | "project" | "person" | "feature" | "task" | "decision" | "question";
```

**Entity Labels** (`EntityBadge.tsx`, lines 4-12):
```typescript
const KIND_LABELS: Record<string, string> = {
  project: "Project",
  feature: "Feature",
  task: "Task",
  decision: "Decision",
  question: "Question",
  person: "Person",
  workspace: "Workspace",
};
```

**Extractable Entities** (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/shared/chat-component-definitions.ts`, line 3):
```typescript
export const extractableKindSchema = z.enum(["project", "person", "feature", "task", "decision", "question"]);
```

---

### 2. COLOR SYSTEM & THEMING

**CSS Variables** (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/styles.css`, lines 19-40):

Entity accent colors (OKLCH color space):
- Project: `oklch(0.65 0.15 250)` — Blue
- Feature: `oklch(0.65 0.15 170)` — Teal
- Task: `oklch(0.70 0.15 145)` — Green
- Decision: `oklch(0.70 0.15 55)` — Amber
- Question: `oklch(0.65 0.15 300)` — Purple
- Person: `oklch(0.65 0.15 25)` — Warm Coral

**Muted Variants** (for backgrounds/badges): `--entity-{kind}-muted`
**Foreground Text**: `--entity-{kind}-fg` (high contrast)

**Graph Transform (Server-side)** (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/server/graph/transform.ts`, lines 5-14):

Resolved hex values for Three.js rendering:
```typescript
case "project": return "#3b82f6";     // oklch(0.65 0.15 250)
case "feature": return "#14b8a6";     // oklch(0.65 0.15 170)
case "task": return "#22c55e";        // oklch(0.70 0.15 145)
case "decision": return "#eab308";    // oklch(0.70 0.15 55)
case "question": return "#a855f7";    // oklch(0.65 0.15 300)
case "person": return "#f97316";      // oklch(0.65 0.15 25)
```

---

### 3. BADGE & TAG COMPONENTS

#### **EntityBadge Component** (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/components/graph/EntityBadge.tsx`, lines 14-26)

```typescript
export function EntityBadge({ kind }: { kind: EntityKind }) {
  return (
    <span
      className="entity-badge-inline"
      style={{
        background: entityMutedColor(kind),
        color: entityColor(kind),
      }}
    >
      {KIND_LABELS[kind] ?? kind}
    </span>
  );
}
```

Uses client-side CSS variables (`--entity-{kind}` and `--entity-{kind}-muted`)

#### **CSS for Entity Badge** (`styles.css`, lines 800-809)

```css
.entity-badge-inline {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.25rem;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-size: 0.67rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  padding: 0.15rem 0.42rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
```

#### **Other Badge-like Components**

- `.seed-kind` (lines 337-347): Used in seed panel — light blue background
- `.entity-card` (lines 519-524): Full entity cards in extraction summary
- `.entity-kind` (lines 532-537): Kind label within entity cards
- `.entity-status` (lines 539-544): Status badge within entity cards

---

### 4. UI COMPONENTS & RENDERING

#### **EntityCard** (Chat Component)
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/chat-component-catalog.tsx`, lines 31-62

Displays:
- Kind (uppercase label)
- Status (right-aligned)
- Name (bold, larger)
- Confidence (decimal to 2 places)
- Optional graph link button

Props (from `chat-component-definitions.ts`, lines 5-11):
```typescript
export const entityCardPropsSchema = z.object({
  kind: extractableKindSchema,
  name: z.string().min(1),
  confidence: z.number().min(0).max(1),
  status: z.string().min(1),
  entityId: z.string().optional(),
});
```

#### **EntityDetailPanel** 
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/components/graph/EntityDetailPanel.tsx`

Sections:
1. Header with badge + title (line 142)
2. Metadata section (lines 148-182)
   - Status
   - Confidence
   - Created date
   - Owner name
   - Priority
3. Rationale section (lines 184-189)
4. Relationships section (line 191, uses `RelationshipList`)
5. Provenance section (line 193)
6. Actions (lines 195-213)
   - Confirm Decision (if status in `["extracted", "proposed", "provisional", "inferred"]`)
   - Override Decision
   - Mark Complete (for tasks)

#### **RelationshipList** 
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/components/graph/RelationshipList.tsx`

Groups relationships by kind + direction, displays with EntityBadge for each related entity

#### **ProvenanceSection**
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/components/graph/ProvenanceSection.tsx`

Shows:
- Source kind (Message or Document chunk)
- Confidence score
- Extracted date
- Evidence quote
- Jump to message link (for messages)

---

### 5. API TYPES & DATA FLOW

#### **Extraction Event** (`contracts.ts`, lines 129-134)
```typescript
export type ExtractionEvent = {
  type: "extraction";
  messageId: string;
  entities: ExtractedEntity[];
  relationships: ExtractedRelationship[];
};
```

#### **ExtractedEntity** (`contracts.ts`, lines 36-43)
```typescript
export type ExtractedEntity = {
  id: string;
  kind: EntityKind;
  text: string;
  confidence: number;
  sourceKind: SourceKind;
  sourceId: string;
};
```

#### **EntityDetailResponse** (`contracts.ts`, lines 206-231)
```typescript
export type EntityDetailResponse = {
  entity: {
    id: string;
    kind: EntityKind;
    name: string;
    data: Record<string, unknown>;  // Flexible for status, priority, etc.
  };
  relationships: Array<{
    id: string;
    kind: EntityKind;
    name: string;
    relationKind: string;
    direction: "incoming" | "outgoing";
    confidence: number;
  }>;
  provenance: Array<{
    sourceId: string;
    sourceKind: "message" | "document_chunk";
    confidence: number;
    extractedAt: string;
    evidence?: string;
    evidenceSource?: string;
    resolvedFrom?: string;
    fromText?: string;
  }>;
};
```

#### **GraphResponse** (`contracts.ts`, lines 201-204)
```typescript
export type GraphResponse = {
  nodes: ReagraphNode[];
  edges: ReagraphEdge[];
};
```

#### **ReagraphNode** (`contracts.ts`, lines 179-188)
```typescript
export type ReagraphNode = {
  id: string;
  label: string;
  fill: string;  // Hex color from transform
  data: {
    kind: EntityKind;
    connectionCount: number;
    status?: string;  // Optional, displayed in graph
  };
};
```

---

### 6. API ENDPOINTS

#### **Entity Detail Route**
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/server/entities/entity-detail-route.ts`

Endpoint: `GET /api/entities/{entityId}?workspaceId={workspaceId}`
- Uses `getEntityDetail()` from graph/queries.ts
- Returns complete EntityDetailResponse

#### **Entity Search Route**
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/server/entities/entity-search-route.ts`

Endpoint: `GET /api/entities/search?workspaceId={id}&q={query}&limit={limit}`
- Supports optional `projectId` parameter for scoped search
- Returns array of `SearchEntityResponse`

#### **Graph Route**
File: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/server/graph/graph-route.ts`

Endpoint: `GET /api/graph/{workspaceId}?[center={entityId}&depth={1-3}|project={projectId}]`
- Uses `transformToReagraph()` to convert DB records to graph visualization format
- Returns GraphResponse

---

### 7. STATE MANAGEMENT

**View State** (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/palembang/app/src/client/stores/view-state.ts`):

Zustand store with:
- `selectedEntityId` — currently selected entity in graph
- `graphViewMode` — "project" or "focused"
- `graphProjectId` — filter by project
- `graphCenterId` — center node for focused view
- `graphDepth` — 1-3, traversal depth
- `highlightMessageId` — message to highlight when jumping from graph

---

### 8. COMPONENT USAGE PATTERNS

#### **In Chat (EntityCard)**
- Shows kind as uppercase label (styled with `.entity-kind`)
- Shows status as uppercase label (styled with `.entity-status`)
- Compact, card-based layout
- Confidence displayed as "Confidence 0.95"

#### **In Graph Detail Panel**
- EntityBadge inline with title (`.entity-badge-inline`)
- Metadata section displays entity properties flexibly
- Status and confidence extracted from `entity.data` object

#### **In Knowledge Graph**
- Nodes colored by `entityColor(kind)` hex values
- Node size based on `connectionCount`
- Status available in node.data but not rendered in graph canvas

---

### 9. KEY FILE LOCATIONS & IMPORTS

| Purpose | File | Key Exports |
|---------|------|------------|
| Type definitions | `/app/src/shared/contracts.ts` | EntityKind, ExtractedEntity, EntityDetailResponse |
| Entity extraction schema | `/app/src/server/extraction/schema.ts` | extractionEntitySchema, ExtractionPromptOutput |
| Chat component defs | `/app/src/shared/chat-component-definitions.ts` | entityCardPropsSchema, extractionSummaryPropsSchema |
| Badge component | `/app/src/client/components/graph/EntityBadge.tsx` | EntityBadge |
| Detail panel | `/app/src/client/components/graph/EntityDetailPanel.tsx` | EntityDetailPanel |
| Graph transform | `/app/src/server/graph/transform.ts` | transformToReagraph, entityColor |
| Theme helpers | `/app/src/client/components/graph/graph-theme.ts` | entityColor, entityMutedColor, edgeStyle |
| Styles | `/app/src/client/styles.css` | --entity-{kind}, .entity-badge-inline, .entity-detail-* |
| View state | `/app/src/client/stores/view-state.ts` | useViewState hook |

---

### 10. DESIGN TOKENS (DESIGN_TOKENS.md)

**Visual Language Principles:**
- Scandinavian clarity, typography-led, content-first
- Entity colors are the *only* non-neutral colors in the product
- Never use raw Tailwind colors — always use entity tokens
- Muted backgrounds + accent left borders for cards
- Graph nodes use accent fill at 80% opacity

**Color Palette:**
- 6 entity types with distinct hues
- Foreground variants for text on colored backgrounds
- Muted variants for subtle indicators and backgrounds

---

This codebase uses a **cohesive design system** where:
1. Entity types are mapped to semantic colors via CSS variables
2. Colors appear consistently in chat cards, graph nodes, badges, and detail panels
3. All entity metadata (status, confidence, etc.) flows through `entity.data` as flexible key-value pairs
4. Reusable components (EntityBadge, EntityCard) ensure consistency across views
5. Server-side transform resolves CSS variables to hex for WebGL rendering

